From b2a98401f3d00170d8b008d713a7e4484ab55d0c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <bramar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 06:27:57 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: mac80211: Apply radio mask changes while the
 network interface is running

In case of  2.4 GHz + 5 GHz MLO, the 5G 40 MHz scan failed because the
radio mask was not set due to netif running check in mac80211, which
led to the VAP failing to come up.

To address this, introduced the changes to ensure the radio mask
is applied even when the interface is active, since dynamic link
addition/removal is supported in MLO scenarios.

Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <bramar@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/wireless/nl80211.c | 7 ++++---
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/wireless/nl80211.c b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
index 01a9a19..62c6602 100644
--- a/net/wireless/nl80211.c
+++ b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
@@ -4946,6 +4946,10 @@ static int nl80211_set_interface(struct sk_buff *skb, struct genl_info *info)
 	err = nl80211_parse_vif_radio_mask(info, &radio_mask);
 	if (err < 0)
 		return err;
+
+	if (radio_mask)
+		wdev->radio_mask = radio_mask;
+
 	if (err && netif_running(dev))
 		return -EBUSY;
 
@@ -4957,9 +4961,6 @@ static int nl80211_set_interface(struct sk_buff *skb, struct genl_info *info)
 	if (!err && params.use_4addr != -1)
 		dev->ieee80211_ptr->use_4addr = params.use_4addr;
 
-	if (radio_mask)
-		wdev->radio_mask = radio_mask;
-
 	if (change && !err)
 		nl80211_notify_iface(rdev, wdev, NL80211_CMD_SET_INTERFACE);
 
